The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 Music for the soul

 Founded by a group of music lovers, Rasika Ranjana Sabha is a premier cultural organisation in the city catering to the cultural needs of its citizens for over six decades. Organising music and dance concerts, mainly Carnatic, and festivals all the year round with a view to promoting and popularising traditional Indian forms, its programmes feature well-known artistes from all over the country. The Sabha also holds regular classes in dance, vocal music and mridangam. To commemorate the 160th anniversary of Saint Thyagaraja, one of the famous music trinities, the Sabha is currently hosting the Gurmajor function. Its on-going 61st annual music festival comprises vocal and instrumental Indian classical music recitals by eminent artistes. This evening, Vishakha Hari will present a sangeetha upanyasam, reciting Sri Sadguru Thyagaraja Charitram. Her maiden performance in the city, she will be accompanied by B. Ananthakrishnan (violin) and Arjun Ganesh (mridangam).

 Event: Musical discourse by Vishakha Hari 

When: Today at 5.30 pm 

Where: Sree Thyagaraja Hall, P-530 Raja Basanta Roy Road 

